==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cornage
<hw>Cor"nage</hw> <pr>(k?r"n?j)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OF.,,
horn-blowing, tax on horned cattle, fr. F. <ets>corne</ets> a horn, L.
<ets>cornu</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Law)</fld> <def>An ancient tenure of
land, which obliged the tenant to give notice of an invasion by blowing
a horn.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cornamute</ent>⟦br⟧
